The United Auto Workers said it plansto tell General Motors Corp later today that it will authorizea strike by its local at GM's truck and bus works in Pontiac,Mich.    The union said its letter to GM means the 9,000 workers atthe Pontiac facility will walk out of the plant next week if acontract dispute is not settled between the two sides.    The action "triggers an intensive effort to resolvedisputed issues before the letter expires," the UAW said.    The main unresolved issue is the subcontracting of work byGM to non-union workers, the union said in a statement.    The UAW said its vice president Donald F. Ephlin, head ofthe union's General Motors bargaining unit, met with officialsof Local 594 in Pontiac, Mich., this morning to review theissues involved in the dispute.    The union said it is "hopeful that a settlement can bereached before a strike becomes necessary." Reuter&#3;